data.title: 'Further Development' of Mendel's legacy? Erich von Tschermak
data.meta_description: The contribution of Erich von Tschermak-Seysenegg (1871-1962) to the beginning of classical genetics is a matter of dispute. The aim of this study is to analyse, based on newly accessible archive materials, the relevance of his positions and theoretical views in a debate between advocates of early M …
